`List[ContractSendSecretReveal]` is not more useful than `List[Event]`. `List[Event]` can take `.append(object_of_another_event)` but `List[ContractSendSecretReveal]` cannot take `.append(object_of_another_event)`. See "List[subclass] is incompatible with List[superclass]" https://github.com/python/mypy/issues/2984 It's because you can update a List in-place.

The alternative is to use a Sequence instead of List.  So we'll be using `(event1, event2, event3)`.  Sequences are not updatable, `Sequence[ContractSendSecretReveal]` is more useful than `Sequence[Event]`.

@LefterisJP Shall we go with `Sequence[ContractSendSecretReveal]` here?

