I understand that you are using the field to help the compiler narrow the types. You use it to narrow FobCardData to one of ScalarFobData or HistogramFobData. It's a nice feature of the TypeScript compiler and we use it elsewhere in the code base.

I think, though, this is a misuse of type narrowing.

The end result in your controller code is that every function effectively looks like this:

```
someFunction() {
